propDescriptions.classes: Override or extend the styles applied to the component. See CSS API below for more details.
propDescriptions.component: The component used for the root node. Either a string to use a HTML element or a component.
propDescriptions.defaultColumns: The default number of columns of the component. This is provided for server-side rendering.
propDescriptions.defaultHeight: The default height of the component in px. This is provided for server-side rendering.
propDescriptions.defaultSpacing: The default spacing of the component. Like spacing, it is a factor of the theme's spacing. This is provided for server-side rendering.
propDescriptions.spacing: Defines the space between children. It is a factor of the theme's spacing.
propDescriptions.sx: Allows defining system overrides as well as additional CSS styles. See the `sx` page for more details.

root.description: Styles applied to the root element.
